88	Sea-Tac Airport to Federal Way Transit Center	  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial">This project would extend Link LRT service south approximately 9.6 miles from Airport Station at Sea-Tac Airport &ldquo; to Federal Way (S. 317th St) in the vicinity of existing Federal  Way Transit  Center, including a new station in Federal Way.&rdquo; </span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"> </span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial">The alignment would be aerial and would continue along International   Blvd after leaving the airport. It would then &ldquo;turn southwest to cross S. 188<sup>th</sup>   St. following along the west side of 28<sup>th</sup> Ave. S. to a station at S. 200<sup>th</sup>   St. This station would include a &ldquo;transit center, kiss and ride facility and 630-space park and ride facility in multi-level parking garage.&rdquo; It would also include bike racks and lockers, bike lanes on S. 200<sup>th</sup>, multiple crosswalks, and potentially restrooms, concessions and a security facility.</span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"> </span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial">The project would then continue 2.3 miles south along the west side of SR 99 to the Kent/Des Moine station adjacent to Highline  Community College at S. 240<sup>th</sup> St., which would be a center platform with a ground-level plaza. It would also include a 500-space park and ride garage linked to the station with an elevated pedestrian walkway, and local bus transfer and passenger drop off facilities. </span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial"> </span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial">The aerial alignment would then continue along SR 99 &ldquo;for 2.5 miles (approx) from Kent-Des Moines Station (S. 240th St) to S. 272nd Street (at existing Redondo Heights Park-and-Ride lot), including a new station at S. 272nd Street.&rdquo; The station would be a center platform with a ground level plaza. A new 500 space parking structure would be constructed in the park-and-ride with a pedestrian bridge across SR 99 connecting to the station. The alignment would then continue an additional 2.8 miles south following the east side of SR 99 until turning east to follow a route between S. 312<sup>th</sup> and S. 316 to the Federal Way station, which would be a center platform with a ground level plaza and a pedestrian bridge to the existing park-and-ride garage. &ldquo;The final alignment and station locations will be determined through project level design and environmental review.&rdquo;</span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial">(Source: Sound Transit project page for S27, S28, S29a, S30 found at: <a href="http://soundtransit.org/x3951.xml">http://soundtransit.org/x3951.xml</a>)</span></p>	Construct an extension of Link light rail from Sea-Tac Airport to Federal Way Transit Center			10107	<p><a href="http://soundtransit.org/Documents/pdf/st2/potential_projects_01_04_2007/S27_-Link-_SeaTac_Airport_to_S_200th_St_DP.pdf" title="Sound Transit Project Page: SeaTac Airport to S. 200th St.">Sound Transit Project Page: SeaTac Airport to S. 200th St.</a></p><p><a href="http://soundtransit.org/Documents/pdf/st2/potential_projects_01_04_2007/S28_-Link-_S_200th_St_to_Kent-Des_Moines_Rd_via_SR_99_DP.pdf" title="Sound Transit Project Page: S. 200th St. to Kent-Des Moines Rd.">Sound Transit Project Page: S. 200th St. to Kent-Des Moines Rd.</a><br /> </p><p><a href="http://soundtransit.org/Documents/pdf/st2/potential_projects_01_04_2007/S29A_-Link-_Kent-Des_Moines_Rd_to_S_272nd_St_via_SR_99_DP.pdf" title="Sound Transit Project Page: Kent-Des Moines Rd. to S. 272nd St.">Sound Transit Project Page: Kent-Des Moines Rd. to S. 272nd St.</a> </p><p><a href="http://soundtransit.org/Documents/pdf/st2/potential_projects_01_04_2007/S30_-Link-_S_272nd_St_to_Federal_Way_TC_via_SR_99_DP